Sarkozy’s Popularity Holds Steady at 36%, LH2 Poll Shows

-- B y   V i d y a   R o o t
-- 
2011-07-11T16:00:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-10/sarkozy-fillon-lose-ground-in-monthly-poll-le-parisien-says.html
French President  Nicolas Sarkozy ’s
popularity was unchanged from June, a poll showed, as 36 percent
of the people surveyed said they had a positive opinion of him.  The president’s popularity rose among women and held steady
at 52 percent among seniors, according to the survey conducted
by pollster LH2 for Le Nouvel Observateur magazine. More people
affected by the financial crisis had a negative opinion of him,
the poll showed. Sarkozy gained 5 points to 87 percent among
supports of his ruling Union for a Popular Movement party.  The poll was conducted over the phone on July 8 and 9, with
957 people aged 18 or more participating. No margin of error was
provided.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Vidya Root in Paris at 
 vroot@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
